eet, 6 inches (76.97 meters) to become the first female Cal athlete to win any Olympic medal in the sport.\\u00c2 \\\"It's a whirlwind of emotions, but the second the competition was over, I felt like I just went into shock,\\\" Rogers told CBC Sports' Devin Heroux.\\u00c2 \\\"I looked up, and I saw my coach and my family, who came all the way here from Richmond, B.C., from New Zealand, from California, and I just felt nothing but love and support and the fact I could share this moment with them is what makes it special for me.\\\"\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.999995439252357, \"rank\": 4.548031660578292e-06, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999058673, \"rank\": 9.39320195097252e-11, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 487, \"end\": 490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 0.9999999994379323, \"rank\": 5.618114527391737e-10, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}, {\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999953184765662, \"rank\": 4.681545210333487e-06, \"text\": \"CBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 775, \"title\":