"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"shock\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 645}, {\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"my coach\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 733}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 849}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In tears afterward, Rogers got hugs from all of her rivals in the field and from her long-time coach at Cal and since, Mo Saatara.\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 1077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1051, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 0.9999999994379323, \"rank\": 5.618114527391737e-10, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tears\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"hugs\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"her rivals\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"her long-time coach\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"Mo Saatara\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cal hadn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t won an individual gold medal in track and field since Guinn Smith took the pole vault gold at the 1948 London Games.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinn_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guinn Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinn_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinn_Smith\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cal\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1082}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual gold medal\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1120}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"the pole vault gold\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1948 London Games\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rogers joins Smith and 400-meter specialist Archie Williams (1936) as the Golden Bears\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 only individual gold-medal winners in track and field.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Archie Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Williams\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"Smith\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"the Golden Bears\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 only individual gold-medal winners\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rogers had to battle from behind twice to win three years after placing fifth at the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She held the early lead with a first-round throw of 243-1 (74.11 meters) before China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Jie Zhou, 21, inched in front with her second-round effort of 243-8 (74.27).\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jie_people\", \"score\": 0.9997223715451405, \"rank\": 0.0002777049814734668, \"text\": \"Jie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jie_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jie_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1551, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhou_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.9772929515139159, \"rank\": 0.021065236623197005, \"text\": \"Zhou\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhou_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhou_dynasty\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the early lead\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1480}, {\"ngram\": \"a first-round throw\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"243-1 (74.11 meters\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1576}, {\"ngram\": \"her second-round effort\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1605}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rogers regained the lead with a third-round effort of 244-4 (74.47) but that didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t last long.\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"a third-round effort\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American\\u00c2 Annette Nneka Echikunwoke, 28, a surprise winner at the U.S. trials, delivered a season-best throw of 247-8 (75.48) to move into the top spot after three rounds.\\u00c2 Rogers drew close to Echikunwoke with a fourth-round throw of 247-6 (75.44) then broke through with her winning mark on her fifth try.\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 2031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nneka_(singer)\", \"score\": 0.9901941897375562, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nneka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nneka_(singer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nneka_(singer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a surprise winner\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. trials\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"a season-best throw\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"the top spot\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"three rounds\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1892}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 Rogers\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"Echikunwoke\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1927}, {\"ngram\": \"a fourth-round throw\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"her winning mark\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"her fifth try\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That throw still short of Rogers\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 personal best of 257-11 (78.62) that ranks her fifth on the all-time world list, but it was farther than either silver-medalist Echikunwoke or bronze winner Zhao have ever gone.\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2225, \"end\": 2229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sima_Zhao\", \"score\": 0.9999889577057124, \"rank\": 1.104240629008488e-05, \"text\": \"Zhao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sima_Zhao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sima_Zhao\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rogers\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-time world list\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"either silver-medalist Echikunwoke\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze winner\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Coming to this moment, getting to that fifth round, it's a moment of do or die,\\\" Rogers told the Canadian Press.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2345, \"end\": 2359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Press\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canadian_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this moment\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"that fifth round\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2313}, {\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To be able to do it when it counts, in that throw, to see my coach cheering from the stands, it's like, 'OK, I think we did it'.\\\"\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2491, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that throw\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"my coach\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2428}, {\"ngram\": \"the stands\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pick of Track and Field News, Sports Illustrated, USA Today and Athletics Weekly to win in Paris, Rogers delivered.\\u00c2 Including four relays, Cal now has seven Olympic gold medals in track and field.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2561, \"end\": 2577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Weekly\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics Weekly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Weekly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Weekly\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999995275175, \"rank\": 4.724644545834468e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 0.9999999994379323, \"rank\": 5.618114527391737e-10, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The pick\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"Track and Field News\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2525}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"USA Today\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2556}, {\"ngram\": \"Rogers\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"four relays\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2635}, {\"ngram\": \"seven Olympic gold medals\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2674}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2683}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most recent of those was by sprinter Eddie Hart on the 4x100 relay at the 1972 Games \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 52 years ago.\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2737, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Hart_(athlete)\", \"score\": 0.9372356799551512, \"rank\": 0.06696428571429688, \"text\": \"Eddie Hart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Hart_(athlete)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Hart_(athlete)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 4x100 relay\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2766}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1972 Games\", \"from\": 2770, \"to\": 2784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also allowed Canada to sweep gold in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hammer after teammate Ethan Katzberg claimed the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s title.\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2821, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999528069224173, \"rank\": 4.719466906351735e-05, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2841}, {\"ngram\": \"the me